					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/daveyoufool" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2034230); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2034230&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610163364" alt="daveyoufool" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2034230)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/daveyoufool" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2034230); return false;" >daveyoufool</a></span> <span class="odate time_1448252654 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">23 Nov 2015 04:24</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2412106">
									

<p>Yes, yes you can.</p>
<p>Corbenic is a huge place meant to be a hub to all the possible afterlives. You end up in the desert when you die, and you make your journey from there, utilizing skills you've learned throughout your life. Your final destination could be good or bad, and it all depends on your choices.</p>
<p>What it needs is -<br />
- More places to go<br />
- More dangers<br />
- More ways in which a human can be permanently trapped in an eternal nasty situation for all eternity, or the omnipresent healing factor could be negated<br />
- More races and creatures and monsters</p>
<p>MTF Omega-16 report transcripts would also be welcome, perhaps a new tab for that is in order. Keep in mind, the majority of them don't know they're not coming back.</p>

							</div>

								
