		<div class="post" id="post-2412800">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2412800)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2412800">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rumetzen" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(209204); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=209204&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610163365" alt="rumetzen" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=209204)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rumetzen" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(209204); return false;" >rumetzen</a></span> <span class="odate time_1448361207 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">24 Nov 2015 10:33</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2412800">
									

<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p>your hand-to-hand combat abilities, skills of judgment, and stamina are all exceptional,</p>
</blockquote>
<p>These can't possibly be the main criteria for doing anything Foundation related. I don't care if earth weapons are available or not.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I am happy to note that none of you have read the documentation for SCP-2922. Hopefully, I will not have to stress the importance of not breaking into a document long since labeled for Level 5 clearance.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>So why even bring it up? &quot;You know that thing you haven't read? Yeah, don't read it.&quot;</p>
<p>I imagine if these people are really such high level operatives they shouldn't need to be super double reminded not to look at documents they're not cleared for.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>and will possess levels of energy that render rest unnecessary. Injuries are also prone to regenerate.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Oh so&#8230; why does stamina matter again?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Corbenic is an extradimensional realm of undefined volume.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>&quot;size&quot; maybe</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Gravity, air, and temperature readings are all similar to that of Earth.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>What the fuck is an &quot;air reading&quot;?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The sky maintains a pea-green color. Weather is generally unchanging, temperature is usually breezy cold.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>&quot;Dark&quot; green. Okay, and when it's not like that it's&#8230; stormy? Typhoons? Radiation storms? Important info, that.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>There are no day or night cycles</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Singular.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>a mountain range known as the Valley of the Striders.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Known by whom?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>through the desert for as long as possible</p>
</blockquote>
<p>That's descriptive.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>dangerous native species of primate - the Striders, its namesake</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Calling Striders primates seems to be highly presumptuous at best.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>believed to be over 30&#160;km in height.</p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>The Chitin Sea</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Seriously, who's naming this shit?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Betrayed the Foundation when we refused to meet special demands regarding her husband.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This is more of an SCP-2922 related complaint, but I really hate this whole story/character arc.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Teleportation to an unknown area, and</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Wouldn't they just be disappearing from existence from our perspective?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>to duty after defecation.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Excretion</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Damn it, she was only 23.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Ahahaha what? Who the fuck cares how old the Agent was, this is the Foundation we're talking about.</p>
<p>As a side note, current pet peeves: Radio communication that doesn't use proper pro words. Also, wait, they can bring radios but not guns? What?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>A bunch of humans in royal clothes piled on her like wild animals and dragged her kicking and screaming into the Marble Hall, tearing her apart with their bare hands.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Who talks like this?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Your fears are irrelevant.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>There's literally no possible way to say this sentence and not sound like an evil overlord.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I'm drunk, you moron.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Yeah we're stuck in an alternate dimension with an important mission, but I <em>guess</em> there's time to get drunk and rant at our superior officer.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>02 can come by too if he wants. It was real scary at first. They were trying to rip my skin open and use it as a hat. But then I saw that it happens to everyone here. The torturers and the tortured switch places all the time. Everyone kills and eats and fucks each other, and it's all one big joke, and I'm dying laughing! This is frickin' amazing.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Seriously, all your dialogue needs rewriting to sound like real people. Also, they're willing to say asshole and dick, but not fucking?</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>This is basically just worldbuilding notes posted on to the main site. It's interesting worldbuilding, but there's no story to make them worth posting. Two paragraphs of cheesy dialogue don't count.</p>

							</div>

								
